// correction. Normalizes `gate_text` before hashing so two retries of the
// same underlying input (e.g. a deck re-extracted with a slightly different
// line-wrap, or OCR noise reflowing whitespace) hash IDENTICALLY: trim the
// ends, collapse every run of whitespace (spaces, tabs, newlines) to one
// space. This is what makes `raw_signals.content_hash` (below) and
// `ai_runs.input_hash` retry-stable rather than accidentally
// input-formatting-stable.
